The paper deals with optimization problems on graphs and metrics, which are typical topics in computer science. The use of matroids and knapsack constraints also suggests a connection to discrete mathematics and combinatorial optimization, which are often studied in the cs.DS and cs.GT sub-categories. The paper also mentions content distribution network applications, which could be related to networking and information theory (cs.IT), as well as outlier versions of the problems, which could be related to data mining and machine learning (cs.NI) or statistical inference (cs.SI).
